Product name: Handmade Wooden Toys Folk Art Wooden Puppet, Hand Carved Wooden Marionette Puppet, Handmade Wooden Puppet, Folk Art Doll, FREE SHIPPING
Description:
This is a vintage 1940s hand carved folk art wooden puppet / wooden marionette. This handmade wooden toy depicts a seemingly grumpy, adorably frowning man with a top hat. This 1940s toy folk art doll is jointed at the shoulders, hips, and knees and has a single metal rod attached to his back to control his movement (not uncommon for primitive handmade marionette puppets). The eyes, eyebrows and ears are very simply drawn on, on this folk art wooden marionette, and the words "hand carved" are written on the back of his head. This handmade wood puppet also has written on the back of his body the puppet maker's name, (Russel Cartee) and the place (Greenup, KY) and date (4-11-44) of his creation. This hand carved folk art toy measures approximately 12.5" tall, 3.25" wide, and 1.5" thick. The metal rod to control him is 17" long. I don't know if it is removable. I haven't attempted it and I'm not going to. I don't want to damage this wonderful little guy.
This is a vintage item with the natural wear, tear, and character flaws of age. Please see the photos for condition, as they are part of the description.

Product name: Vintage 1962 Bugs Bunny Jack-in-the-Box Toy in Near Pristine  Condition - Plays Hail, Hail, The Gangs All  Here
Description:
This vintage 1962 Bugs Bunny jack-in-the-box toy is in near-pristine 
condition.  The paint on all six sides is bright with no marring of the 
surfaces, no rust or dents.  The music box still plays the Ted Duncan 
arrangement of "Hail, hail the gang's all here" and Bugs pops up out of 
the box.  Bugs is sans ears, but still retains his cheeky "What's up, 
Doc" attitude!   This colorful, historical toy is perfect for Bugs Bunny 
collectors, Looney Tunes aficionados, or to decorate your 60s-style 
rabbit hole!
Ted Duncan got credit for the idea of the music-maker device within the 
Uke-A-Doodle. In the 1940s, Duncan was known in Hollywood for 
orchestrating music for several popular movies, but he also collected 
expensive Swiss music boxes as a hobby. In studying how music boxes 
operated, he came up with an idea for an affordable music-making device. 
He built a prototype and approached Mattel with his invention. Elliot 
Handler, president of Mattel, loved the device and not only added the 
music maker to the Uke-A-Doodle, but also included it in a variety of 
Mattel toys, most notably the Mattel Jack-In-The-Boxes.

Product name: Vintage Barney Kite String in Original Package  FREE U.S. SHIPPING
Description: This is the perfect gift for a 90s kid who was a fan of the Big Purple (in my opinion more of a pink or magenta) dinosaur. It's even in its original packaging-- I found it in a cabinet at my parent's house, it was probably picked up as a spare, my brother and I loved to fly kites, and even though neither of us were Barney fans (we used to tease my little cousin mercilessly about his Barney and Power Ranger afflictions) we would have used this spare string in a pinch because it's on a good holder, not one of the cheap plastic ones that came with the kites we'd buy at the supermarket. It would make a great gag gift for an adult--especially in March, a great time in so many places to fly kites, or for a trip to a destination like San Juan, PR where the trade winds make kite flying a year round hobby. Product name: Huge Go Fly A KITE "NEWPORT SAILBOAT" 58" x 68" Rip Stop Nylon Sail Hull Waves 1980's Vintage New Old Stock stored since store closed
Description:
Offering a 1980's vintage NEWPORT SAILBOAT KITE made by GO FLY A KITE Company, East Haddam, CT.  This rip-stop nylon kite consists of two components:  a 39.5" x 68" isosceles triangular-shaped "SAIL" and an 18""HULL" with STREAMERS (ie, waves of water?) connected by metal hooks; total assembled height is 58". As to assembly: 
- the 38.5" dowel with hooks spans across the center of the back of the sail (use grommets) 
- a pair of 3' dowels are inserted one each into the sides of the sail  
- a set of dowels with a connector are inserted into the top of the hull 
- the hull with streamers is attached at three points (grommets) to the sail.
Although there are two areas of minor spots, this is NOS (New Old Stock) having been on display in my toy shop and stored since it closed; it has never been flown.  Also, there is a tiny pinhole in the yellow part, most likely shipped thus.  It would be quite fun to fly in Rhode Island!

Description:
Ahoy Sailor!  This 2-piece vintage 1940s Cracker Jack sailor suit is a wardrobe must.  Made from deep navy blue wool, the trousers button up the front with 13 anchor buttons, lace up the back and have 2 front pockets and one back pocket.  The jacket has a pocket on the left chest, red chevrons on the left sleeve, an engineer patch on the right sleeve and a patch for the seaman's ship: U.S.S. Amphion.  The neck of the jacket is line with white stripes, the flap on the back has 2 stars and the sleeves are finished with cuffs that have 3 white stripes and 2 anchor buttons each.  There are 2 pinholes in the trousers, one on the front left leg and one on the back of the left leg, above the cuff (photos are available upon request).  The suit is freshly dry cleaned and is in excellent vintage condition.

Description:
# 3  
This is an original Mattel 1967 straight hair Mrs Beasley doll. She has been cleaned and restored to talk  She was "Buffy's" doll in the 1960s hit show "Family affairs.  She has a full head of original straight blond rooted hair. She has a cloth body and vinyl hands and head and is approximately 21-22 inches tall. She has an original apron with tag, and collar made from another original donor Mrs. Beasley body. She also has her original "Mattel" tag on her bum (its a bit faded but legible), and yellow feet. This Mrs. Beasley has been cleaned and her original stuffing also cleaned and replaced inside her. She smells nice. She has been repaired to talk and does so clearly. She has 2 very small spots on her back that are faint stains, see back pic. She has No tears and one very small repair to right arms machine stitched from the inside, barely noticeable. She will come wearing her tiny, black repro glasses. Her face has a tiny superficial rub to her left cheek does not look bad at all, see pics. Her hands are very nice with all her fingers intact. Her string goes in and out with ease. She says all her different familiar saying in her original endearing granny voice and speaks clearly. Mrs Beasley is priced to reflect any issues mentioned.
Some of her phrases:"My name is Mrs Beasley would you like to play? If you were a little smaller I could rock you to sleep., If you had 3 wishes, what would you wish for?, Would you like to try on my glasses? You may if you wish, Speak a little louder dear so Mrs Beasley can hear you., Long ago I was a little girl just like you, It would be such fun to play jump rope don't you think?,I do think your the nicest little friend I've ever had." 
This sale is for Mrs. Beasley doll, her apron and collar, and her glasses only. She will come in a new clear plastic bag tied with yellow ribbons and her operating instructions attached. She comes as a special gift for yourself or someone special.

Product name: Early 1900's Bontems Bird in a Gilded Cage French Automaton
Description:
This "Bird in a Gilded Cage" was made in France probably around 1910  or so.  It is a mechanical marvel that has been delighting admirers for generations with its flutter of activity: head turning, tail flapping and beak moving to the birds bright song.  Everything is original and I am always careful when soft-brush dusting the leaves and bird's feathers and the velvet floor to the cage. The brass hasn't been thoroughly polished in many years but is in great condition with no dings or dents.  The bottom is stamped "Made in France" with a number and the number 132 appears above the on/off operating lever.  On its feet the cage is 11 inches tall, 12 inches including its ring, and the base is about 6 inches wide.  
The price includes shipping within the United States.

Product name: Stump Table - stump stool, log end table, log table, log stool, rustic decor, rustic home decor, cabin furniture, cabin decor, rustic decor
Description:
Stump Table - Log stools and end tables that are beautifully sanded but preserve the natural characteristics of the tree. MADE TO ORDER - each one varies depending on the log character.
The wood is salvaged, standing dead, dry, lodgepole pine from the Colorado Rocky Mountains.We obtain non merchantable trees, not suitable for milling because they have too many knots, they're curved, or twisted and checked. These are trees that would otherwise be left in the forest to rot. Widths will vary somewhat from the described dimensions do to the nature of this being a natural product.
This is a log, a piece of an unprocessed natural tree, it has cracks, checks, knots, branches broken off, pieces splintered off, saw and tool marks from the harvesting process, and coloration and shapes will vary drastically from one tree to the next. If you are not okay with these natural variations then this product will not be right for you and we ask that you please refrain from ordering this. Please do read our shop policies, they are written to inform customers that might not be familiar with a natural product such as this as these variations might not be readily apparent from pictures in design magazines.
If you need sizes different than listed request a custom order.
If you'd like to try your hand at finishing these yourself we also offer them cut level on our mill, but unpeeled, unsanded, and unfinished: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/270383161/diy-stump-table-finish-your-own-stump?ref=shop_home_active_17

The frames are handmade from either solid walnut or poplar that I source locally and mill myself. The basic profiles are a thin, mid-century modern style that compliments the botanicals but doesn't detract from their natural beauty. The Walnut is finished to allow the natural beauty of the wood to show through. The poplar is offered in a black or gray finish that imparts the feel of a set of frames from generations ago. For the person looking for a very authentic 19th century look, the antique black with gilded silver lip is a gorgeous option. I finish and gild the frames in my shop, made to order, which is what sets these apart from any imported, mass produced frame. The attention to detail on all my frames will definitely be something you will notice!

Description:
ABOUT BUSY BOARDS
The busy board is both a great developmental tool and an engaging fun toy for children ages 10 months to 3 years. Watch your little one play for hours while learning about the world around them!
Leave it on the floor or hang it on the wall -- the busy board is high quality, durable product that can be enjoyed for years and years.

CUSTOMIZE YOUR BUSY BOARD
Personalize your busy board by putting your child’s name on it and by choosing either a gender specific or gender neutral theme. In the "NOTE" section of your cart please indicate your color scheme (boys', girls', gender neutral) and your child's name. If your child's name is longer than 5 letters we recommend the 22x30" board to fit their full name across the board. Listed below are the standard features of our busy boards. 
The standard stations on our 18x24” busy board (as pictured on the Naya & Clark boards) are: Letters spelling out your child’s name, a door that reveals a (non-glass) mirror behind it, a wheel, a zipper, a call bell, a bottle cap, a door chain, a barrel bolt, a padlock, a phone receiver, and a door knocker. In addition to the listed stations, our 22x30” busy board (as pictured on the Summer & Vincent boards) may also include: A light switch, a combination lock, a deadbolt lock and/or a door handle, a bubble mirror, stackable spoons, and a tambourine. Every busy board is a unique made to order piece. Each board is one of a kind and may vary from the one pictured above.
Great care is taken to make sure our boards are child safe. Every board is sanded to a smooth finish and there are no protruding sharp edges from any of the objects included on the board. However, as with any toy, for child's safety, adult supervision is necessary when playing.

♡ PRODUCTION PROCESS 
We will tell you about the process in which our terrariums are born. At first we create the 3D sample using the software “Autodesk 3ds Max”. Then, the image is transposed to the transparent glass, 2mm thick and is very carefully cut by hand. After that, all the details are grinded and wrapped with a special foil. After that there comes the most responsible stage of soldering separate pieces of glass into the shape with ideal proportions. And the final stage – wash thoroughly, grind the seams, patinize (color the seams) and fix. Then the ready terrarium is carefully polished and placed into its personal packaging for the safe transportation and is sent to its new home :-)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
♡ PRODUCTION PERIOD 
Each terrarium is produced personally for you. From the very beginning and till the ready item – it is handmade. Therefore, we will need some time to send your order. Generally the production period takes 4-8 days, depending upon the order complexity and our load. As soon as your order is sent – you receive the notification from Etsy on your mail.

♡ PACKAGE 
We thoroughly pack our products into several layers of air bubble film and special filler and put into the thick carton box. They thoroughly protect the glass forms from any damages, connected with the transportation, therefore, you have nothing to worry about :)
If you wish to send your order as a gift, we will be glad to pack it into the gift pack, and if you wish, will attach a personal note. Please, in this case, write us the text of your note when making your order or in the private message.

Further info regarding raw timber products:
These are rustic in character. 
Most products are made from burned and standing timber from the Black Forest, Colorado Fire of 2013. The wood has been air dried, sanded on one side, and varnished completely, and cracks are normal, often one larger and a few smaller, occasionally even after finishing. They are semi-fragile and should be handled and stored with care. Occasionally bark will chip off or come loose and can easily be fixed with wood glue and a large rubber band. All products are hand-crafted, not factory made so color and shape variations are common. Every piece is unique. Some slight curving or twisting is also possible. Very rarely a tiny grub bug remains in the product, so a slice of cardboard or cloth is advised on the cake stands.

L' estrazione avviene riscaldando il solvente contenuto nel matraccio, dopo che il campione è stato posto nel ditale filtrante nell' interno dell' estrattore. I vapori sviluppati dal calore salgono lungo il tubo laterale, entrano nel corpo centrale per poi salire nel refrigerante. Nel refrigerante si condensano e ricadono allo stato liquido nel ditale, riempendo mano a mano l' estrattore fino al livello del sifone, il quale a sua volta scaricherà il liquido nel matraccio.

• TYPE OF FOLDS? 
• • Straight cut - No fold. Straight cut labels are usually sewn on all 4 sides, the top, or on
left and right side only. No extra charge for this fold.  
• • End fold - Endfold  labels are folded down on the left and right side. They are applied the
same way as straight cut labels, but have a softer edge. Sewing contractors may charge
more for this fold, so please consult them before making your ﬁnal decision. This fold does require an extra charge.
• • Loop Fold - These labels are folded in the top and bottom,usually sewn in bottom T-shirt. Loop fold labels can also be used for sleeve and hem labels.  
• • Centerfold - These labels are folded in the middle and usually sewn into a seam.
Centerfold labels can also be used for sleeve and hem labels. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Book cover fold - These labels are folded in the middle and end fold ,  can also be used for sleeve and hem labels. usually sewn in bottom T-shirt. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Miter Fold - With miter fold labels, the ends are folded under and up, creating a tab to be sewn into a seam. This fold does require an extra charge.
••  Manhattan Fold - Manhattan fold is just like a centerfold label, except the top of the
label is folded down, creating a flap to tuck the bottom fold into.  If you need HEM LABELS we highly recommend the manhattan fold! This fold requires an extra charge.

This is industry standard for woven labels. With weaving, it is impossible to have 100% detail to match your graphic art, as these are literally stitched/woven labels and NOT printed labels.  
The size after cut and folded finished both have -2mm tolerances. The colors of yarn can have tolerances of up to15%.   please note that vertical line, horizontal line  circles, curves and slants are very tough with weaving, it will have a step to the next stitch line in the weaving process. Also, some letters may be larger, etc.   
If you need 100% matching of fine detail, no color of yarn "peeking" through a white background from yarn, you need printed labels instead of premium woven. The yarn/threads of woven labels may have different thicknesses hence limitations to some fine detail. By ordering woven labels you understand and agree with these industry standard tolerances and are approved by you the customer upon placing this order. The method of weaving labels involves moving parts and moving loom machinery and therefore the possibility of the above variances These are NOT printed labels!  While we try our best to avoid any tolerance, these tolerances above are industry standard for all woven labels.

Product name: Tennessee Whiskey Barrel and Ebony Wood Ring - Whiskey Barrel Ring Mens Wedding Band Womens Wooden Wedding Engagement Ring Wood Anniversary
Description:
A unique solid wood ring for the whiskey drinker in your life!
This is a hand-turned oak and ebony wood ring cut from used Jack Daniels whiskey barrels combined with dark black Gaboon ebony wood, custom made to your specifications - choose the size, width, and shape from the options to create your own handmade ring!  Your ring will have a similar look to those in the pictures but each ring is a unique piece of wood with it's own unique patterning with no two exactly alike!  Please note the variability in coloring in the photos, your ring may be lighter or darker than the first image.
 If you'd prefer a ring with just whiskey barrel wood that doesn't include the ebony edges, check out the other options available in my shop: 
http://www.hawkinshandicrafts.etsy.com
After a Jack Daniels barrel is no longer of use to the distillery, it is sold to a number of craftsmen who make everything from planters to knife handles from the wood - or, in this case, a solid wood ring.   I purchase the barrels straight from the distillery general store and have them shipped to my doorstep, where I dismantle them into individual staves to be cut into rings.
  
Each ring is hand polished and finished with several layers of cyanoacrylate.  While many crafters use oils and waxes to finish their rings, cyanoacrylate provides a stronger bond within the wood grain, provides protection from water, and reduces the likelihood of scratching - a common issue with other finishing materials.
To order a pair of rings:  add the first ring to your cart with the correct size/shape information, return to this page, then add another ring with the second size/shape information.
Dimensions:
Ring Size:  5-13.  If you need a larger or smaller size, please inquire using the "Ask a Question" button in the Cart area of the page.
Width:  6mm-9mm
Processing times:  Processing times change depending on my current backlog.  Please see the shop announcement on my homepage for current times to ship!
As with all wood rings, this material is less durable than a traditional metal ring, but with proper care and maintenance, it will look beautiful and last for years!
Size exchanges:  We offer the first size exchange free for residents of the United States (return shipping of the original is your responsibility).  Further alterations to size will incur an additional fee to cover the cost of shipping and handling.

Description:
This listing is for one pair of Quartz Point crystal earweights in oxidized copper. To be worn through tunnel or eyelet jewelry in stretched lobes 2g or larger. Not for unhealed or freshly stretched bare lobes. Wear in fully healed bare lobes 0g or larger only. 
These are raw, natural crystal points and while they are hand-selected to create roughly matched pairs, they are not identical, but have unique characteristics.   The copper is polished to a shine and oxidized, and the patina will continue to evolve over time.
They measure 2 1/4" in diameter on the outside, and 2" in diameter on the inside.  The copper wire is 3mm thick. The Quartz crystals are 1 1/2" tall and just under 1" wide.  
Each weight weighs 30 grams.
From the Cold Forest Collection: Ice Drops.
When the Sun moves low in the sky, the Ice Queen emerges from her caves in the North to descend over the tips of mountains, across treelines, deep into valleys and streams. She moves like a whisper and silences the rushings of life with her white blankets. Caught in her grasp, transfixed for ages, trees turn to brittle splinters, and water as hard as stone.  
See the rest of the Cold Forest collection here:
https://www.etsy.com/shop/QueryEve?section_id=20588087
•••
ELECTRO MAGICK:
 I create jewelry and curiosities by "growing" copper onto crystals and other organics using an alchemical hybrid process:  Electroforming.  In my cauldron of neon blue electrolyte solution, I brood over, coax, and observe my creations as they begin to take shape.  The process takes twelve hours, up to three days, with each piece forming bumps, nodules, lines, and deep grooves along the way.  Some of my pieces are darkened with a Liver of Sulfur solution and polished with oil; others are left shiny and bare.  All of my pieces are left unsealed, which allows them to continue to age and oxidize, giving you a living, breathing adornment that is truly dynamic and ever-changing.
CARE FOR YOUR PIECE: 
  Please handle your handmade jewelry with care; avoid dropping it or inflicting heavy trauma or stress. While copper is sturdy enough for daily wear, it is a softer metal and can be misshapen under stress. Crystals and gemstones, especially in raw form, also need to be treated kindly. Avoid submersion in water and direct exposure to lotions, oils, perfumes, and harsh cleaners. These can permanently discolor some stones or tarnish the copper. To clean your jewelry, simply buff gently with a soft cloth to remove perspiration and oils.  Some people with certain chemistry experience temporary discoloration of the skin when wearing copper jewelry, especially on the fingers and the back of the neck. This is the "Green Ghost" of oxidation and can be washed off the skin with soap and warm water, if you desire.
